{"questionId":"4157","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A magnifying glass is constructed from a thin converging lens.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A converging lens can also be used to produce an image of a distant object. The base&nbsp;of the object is positioned on the principal axis of the lens at a distance of 10.0 m from&nbsp;the centre of the lens. The lens has a focal length of 2.0 m.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Determine the position of the image.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{1}{{10}} + \\frac{1}{v} = \\frac{1}{2}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>10</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mi>v</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><em>v</em> = 2.5&nbsp;«m»</p>","meta":{"questionId":"4157","referenceCode":"17N.3.SL.TZ0.9b.i","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Determine the position of the image.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option C: Imaging","Option C: Imaging","Option C: Imaging (Core topics)","C.1 – Introduction to imaging","Option C: Imaging","Option C: Imaging (Core topics)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}